}}'''赫伯特·贝亚德·斯沃普'''（Herbert Bayard Swope Sr，{{bd|1882年|1月5日|1958年|6月20日}}）是美国编辑、记者。斯沃普的大部分职业生涯都在《{{link-en|纽约世界报|New York World}}》度过。他是第一个三次获得{{link-en|普利策报道奖|Pulitzer Prize for Reporting}}的人<ref name="bio">{{Cite web|title=Herbert Bayard Swope Biography|url=http://www.bookrags.com/biography/herbert-bayard-swope-dlb|accessdate=15 January 2018|quote=Herbert Bayard Swope was called the greatest reporter of his time by Lord Northcliffe of the London Daily Mail. The accolade is all the more impressive when one considers that Swope's illustrious colleagues included [[沃尔特·李普曼|沃尔特·李普曼]], {{link-en|Damon Runyon}}, {{link-en|Heywood Broun}}, {{link-en|Alexander Woollcott}}, {{link-en|Franklin P. Adams}}, {{link-en|William Henry Chamberlin}}, {{link-en|Arthur Brisbane}}, and {{link-en|Richard Harding Davis}}. That Swope had a special impact upon journalism in his time is undeniable. He rose rapidly from obscurity to become a journalistic legend|archive-date=2021-02-27|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210227122342/http://www.bookrags.com/biography/herbert-bayard-swope-dlb/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。斯沃普還是[[冷戰|冷戰]]一詞的發明人<ref>{{cite news|1=|first=William|last=Safire|authorlink=William Safire|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2006/10/01/opinion/01iht-edsafire.2988871.html|title=Islamofascism Anyone?|work=[[纽约时报|纽约时报]]|accessdate=2020-09-04|archive-date=2020-01-07|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200107060603/https://www.nytimes.com/2006/10/01/opinion/01iht-edsafire.2988871.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

